{"tag":"section","attrib":{"id":"id907372d1-2930-11f1-8918-be39dde81dc6","identifier":"/us/usc/t22/s4201"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"4201"},"text":"§ 4201.","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" Fees for certification of invoices","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Fees for the consular certification of invoices shall be, and they are, included with the fees for official services for which the President is authorized by ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t22/s4219"},"text":"section 4219 of this title","children":[],"tail":" to prescribe rates or tariffs."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":null},{"tag":"sourceCredit","attrib":{"id":"id907372d2-2930-11f1-8918-be39dde81dc6"},"text":"(","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/act/1906-04-05/ch1366/s9"},"text":"Apr. 5, 1906, ch. 1366, § 9","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/34/101"},"text":"34 Stat. 101","children":[],"tail":".)"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"notes","attrib":{"type":"uscNote","id":"id907372d3-2930-11f1-8918-be39dde81dc6"},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"note","attrib":{"role":"crossHeading","topic":"editorialNotes","id":"id907372d4-2930-11f1-8918-be39dde81dc6"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"b","attrib":{},"text":"Editorial Notes","children":[],"tail":null}],"tail":null}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"codification","id":"id907372d5-2930-11f1-8918-be39dde81dc6"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"Codification","children":[],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Section was not enacted as part of the Foreign Service Act of 1980 which comprises this chapter.","children":[],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"A further provision of section 9 of act ","children":[{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1906-04-05"},"text":"Apr. 5, 1906","children":[],"tail":", repealed R.S. § 2851, which provided for certification of invoices of imported merchandise by the collector of the post, and R.S. § 1721, which prescribed a fee of one dollar to be charged by the consul-general for the British North American provinces, for certifying invoices of goods not exceeding $100 in value."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Section was formerly classified to ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t22/s1181"},"text":"section 1181 of this title","children":[],"tail":", and prior thereto to "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t22/s84"},"text":"section 84 of this title","children":[],"tail":"."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":null}
